STATE of Louisiana
v.
Rory DIMES No. 2018-KH-1404 Supreme Court of Louisiana. January 14, 2019 ON SUPERVISORY WRITS TO THE CRIMINAL DISTRICT COURT, PARISH OF ORLEANS PER CURIAM:

Reconsideration granted; writ granted. The application is transferred to the court of appeal to consider as a timely filed application for supervisory writs concerning the district court's April 15, 2018 denial of his application for post-conviction relief. See State ex rel. Johnson v. Maggio , 440 So.2d 1336 , 1337 (La. 1983).
